Constructor Detail

MagSweepEffectDefinition

public MagSweepEffectDefinition(int duration,
                                int magnitude,
                                int style,
                                int attackTime,
                                int attackLevel,
                                int fadeTime,
                                int fadeLevel,
                                int actuatorIndex)
Initializes this MagSweep effect with the given parameters.

Parameters:
duration - Duration of the effect in milliseconds. To specify an infinite duration, use ImmVibe.VIBE_TIME_INFINITE. For a finite duration, the effect duration goes from zero to the value returned by Device.getCapabilityInt32 for the ImmVibe.VIBE_DEVCAPTYPE_MAX_EFFECT_DURATION device capability type, inclusive.
magnitude - Magnitude of the effect. The effect magnitude goes from ImmVibe.VIBE_MIN_MAGNITUDE to ImmVibe.VIBE_MAX_MAGNITUDE, inclusive.
style - Style of the effect. The effect style must be one of
  • ImmVibe.VIBE_STYLE_SMOOTH
  • ImmVibe.VIBE_STYLE_STRONG
  • ImmVibe.VIBE_STYLE_SHARP
  • ImmVibe.VIBE_DEFAULT_STYLE
attackTime - Attack time of the effect in milliseconds. The attack time goes from zero to the value returned by Device.getCapabilityInt32 for the ImmVibe.VIBE_DEVCAPTYPE_MAX_ENVELOPE_TIME device capability type, inclusive.
attackLevel - Attack level of the effect. The attack level goes from ImmVibe.VIBE_MIN_MAGNITUDE to ImmVibe.VIBE_MAX_MAGNITUDE, inclusive.
fadeTime - Fade time of the effect in milliseconds. The fade time goes from zero to the value returned by Device.getCapabilityInt32 for the ImmVibe.VIBE_DEVCAPTYPE_MAX_ENVELOPE_TIME device capability type, inclusive.
fadeLevel - Fade level of the effect. The fade level goes from ImmVibe.VIBE_MIN_MAGNITUDE to ImmVibe.VIBE_MAX_MAGNITUDE, inclusive.
actuatorIndex - Index of the actuator on which to play the effect when the effect is in an IVTMagSweepElement, and the IVTMagSweepElement is in an IVTBuffer, and the effect is played from the IVTBuffer using Device.playIVTEffect on a composite device supporting effects targeting multiple actuators simultaneously. This value is not used when playing the effect on its own, outside of an IVTBuffer, even when played on a composite device. The actuator index goes from zero to ImmVibe.VIBE_MAX_LOGICAL_DEVICE_COUNT.

getDuration

public int getDuration()
Gets the duration of this MagSweep effect definition.

Returns:
Duration of the effect in milliseconds. If the effect duration is infinite, this method returns ImmVibe.VIBE_TIME_INFINITE. For a finite duration, this method returns a value from zero to the value returned by Device.getCapabilityInt32 for the ImmVibe.VIBE_DEVCAPTYPE_MAX_EFFECT_DURATION device capability type, inclusive.

Sets the actuator index of this MagSweep effect definition.

Parameters:
actuatorIndex - Index of the actuator on which to play the effect when the effect is in an IVTMagSweepElement, and the IVTMagSweepElement is in an IVTBuffer, and the effect is played from the IVTBuffer using Device.playIVTEffect on a composite device supporting effects targeting multiple actuators simultaneously. The actuator index goes from zero to ImmVibe.VIBE_MAX_LOGICAL_DEVICE_COUNT.
